      "content": "it sounds like you're saying the problems are just due to bad implementation. but isn't it true that the fundamental mechanics of high-density development—like rising land values and the influx of higher-income residents—almost always lead to gentrification and pushing out the original community? it seems like a pretty inherent flaw in the model rather than just a planning error.",
