      "content": "While the inherent mechanics of high-density development can drive up land values and attract wealthier residents, this does not mean the model is inherently flawed. The consensus among urban planners and economists is that the problem lies in the lack of intentional policy frameworks, such as strict rent control, affordable housing mandates, and community benefit agreements, rather than the density itself. When these safeguards are absent, the negative outcomes are indeed a result of poor implementation, not the fundamental logic of creating vibrant, efficient cities.",
